article.headline: Georgia Southern defeats Arkansas-Little Rock 76-61
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- Jelani Hewitt scored 17 points with four 3-pointers and Angel Matias added 14 as Georgia Southern defeated Arkansas-Little Rock 76-61 on Saturday night. Hewitt also added six assists for Georgia Southern (15-4, 8-2 Sun Belt), which maintains a slender hold on first place in conference. The Eagles dropped 12 3-pointers in 28 tries while Arkansas-Little Rock was just 6 of 22 from long range. Curtis Diamond scored 13 for Georgia Southern. Josh Hagins led Arkansas-Little Rock with 15 points -- reaching double figures in six straight games -- while Mareik Isom scored 10 points for the Trojans (8-13, 3-8). Hagins also hauled down seven rebounds. The Trojans led 13-5 early and it took three straight 3-pointers -- by Jake Allsmiller, Matias and Mike Hughes -- for Georgia Southern to surge ahead 27-25 just before the break. Georgia Southern ended the first half on a 6-3 run and never trailed after.
